Aim

To transfer data from one memory block to another.

Theory
MOV instruction transfers data
Indirect addressing uses R0/R1
Registers act as pointers
DJNZ used for looping
Efficient for block transfer
Used in memory operations
Fast execution
Simulator Used

EdSim51

Code
ORG 0000H
MOV R0, #30H
MOV R1, #40H
MOV R2, #10

BACK:
MOV A, @R0
MOV @R1, A
INC R0
INC R1
DJNZ R2, BACK

SJMP $
END
Observation
Data copied from 30H–3FH to 40H–4FH
Loop executed 16 times
No data loss
Correct transfer verified
Conclusion

Thus, block data transfer was successfully implemented.
